U.S. Annual industrial wood product in conventional units of measure.

U.S. Annual industrial wood product in conventional units of measure. :(units are in Million feet squared 3/8in.):

ince1

Format

A data frame with 151 observations of 25 variables

  • SW.Ply (Softwood Plywood units: million ft^2, 3/8 in)
  • OSB.Wafer.board (OSB/ Wafer board units: million ft^2, 3/8 in)
  • Lam.Ven.Lumb(Laminated Veneer lumber units: million ft^3)
  • HW.Ply.Ven(Hardwood, Plywood and veneer units: million ft^2, 3/8 in)
  • SW.Lumb(Softwood lumber units: million bd. ft.)
  • HW.Lumb(Hardwood lumber units: million bd. ft.)
  • Lumb.Pallet.Plant(Lumber made at Pallet plants units: million bd. ft.)
  • PartBoard.Prod(Particalboard production units: million ft^2, 3/4 in.)
  • Hardboard.Prod(Hardboard production units: million ft^2, 1/8 in.)
  • MDF.Pro(MDF production units: million ft^2, 3/4 in.)
  • Pulp.Paper.Board(Pulp, paper and board production units: Thousand tons)
  • Other.Products(Other industrial products units: million ft^3)
  • InsulatingBoard(Insulating board units: million ft^2, 1/2 in.)
  • Fuelwood(Fuelwood units: million ft^3)
  • FuelwoodT(Fuelwood units: Thousand short tons)
  • Log.Chip.Exports(Log and Chip exports units: Thousand short tons)
  • RW.Dom.Prod(Roundwood Equivalent of Domestic Product Output units: Thousand short tons)
  • Estimated.Tot.Dom.Timber(Estimated Total Domestic Timber Harvest units: Thousand short tons)

Source

Sources listed on the excel spread from the National Forest Services
